{"name":"Eynon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>Enniaun</i>, an old Welsh personal name ultimately derived from Late Latin <i>Annianus</i>, but also associated with Welsh <i>einion</i> ‘anvil’, taken as implying stability and fortitude. See also   Beynon   and compare   Onion  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Beynon","meanings":["Welsh (southern): variant of   Bennion  ."]},{"name":"Hennion","meanings":["Welsh: from a hypercorrected form of the Welsh personal name <i>Ennion</i>, see   Eynon  .","Flemish and French (mainly Nord): from a pet form of the personal name   Henri   or <i>Jehen</i> (see   Jean  )."]},{"name":"Bennion","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Einion</i>, <i>ap Eynon</i> ‘son of <i>Einion</i>’ (see   Eynon  )."]},{"name":"Binion","meanings":["Traditional: originally a byname meaning ‘anvil’."]},{"name":"Kenyon","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin a local name from any of various places so called. The one in Devon gets its name from the British river name <i>Kenn</i> + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’ the one in north-west London is from the Old English personal name <i>Cēna</i> + <i>tūn</i>; the one in Northumberland is from Old English <i>cyne-</i> ‘royal’ + <i>tūn</i>."]}]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: originally a byname from a vocabulary word meaning ‘eminent, conspicuous’; it was common in the Middle Ages and was revived in the 20th-century."],"variants":[{"name":"Hywell","meanings":["Traditional: originally a byname from a vocabulary word meaning ‘eminent, conspicuous’; it was common in the Middle Ages and was revived in the 20th-century."]},{"name":"Howell","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Welsh name Hywel , or a transferred use of the surname derived from that name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eynon ap Hywel was born about 1320, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Hywel ap Griffith, was 32 and his mother, Mrs. HOWELL ap Griffith, was 27. He married Mrs. ap HOWELL Eynon about 1350, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1320–":"umbes 1320–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1324–Male":"1324–Surnud","1322–Female":"1322–Surnud","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","Abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","ABT 1355":"umbes 1355","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","Abt 1319":"umbes 1319","1290":"1290","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Gwyr, Glamorgan, Wales":"Gwyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1320–":"noin 1320–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1324–Male":"1324–Kuollut","1322–Female":"1322–Kuollut","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","Abt 1350":"noin 1350","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","ABT 1355":"noin 1355","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","Abt 1319":"noin 1319","1290":"1290","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gwyr, Glamorgan, Wales":"Gwyr, Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1320–":"environ 1320–Décédé","1320–Male":"1320–Décédé","1324–Male":"1324–Décédé","1322–Female":"1322–Décédée","1355–Male":"1355–Décédé","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","Abt 1350":"environ 1350","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","Abt 1320":"environ 1320","ABT 1355":"environ 1355","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","Abt 1319":"environ 1319","1290":"1290","Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-